A former Director-General of Nigeria Insurers Association, Prof. Moses Olorunfumi Adeyemi, has died. He was 77. The former Legal Adviser of National Insurance Corporation of Nigeria (NICON) and visiting Professor of Insurance, University of Gambia, died yesterday morning at Eko Hospital, Lagos, after a brief illness. The erudite lawyer was an alumnus of University of Lagos, and a pastor of Christ Apostolic Church, Ebute Meta. A statement by his daughter, Mrs. Jumoke Ifaturoti, said the deceased will be buried on July 12 at his home in Okun-Owa, Odogbolu Local Government of Ogun State after a funeral service to be conducted by Christ Apostolic Church of Nigeria.